library(ggplot2)
counts <- read.csv("/home/abhi/Desktop/sw48.csv", row.names = 1, header =  TRUE, sep = ",")

counts
counts <- counts[which(rowSums(counts) > 10),]
counts
condition <- factor(c("cancer","cancer","treatment","treatment"))

colData <- data.frame(row.names = colnames(counts),condition)

colData
all(rownames(colData) == colnames(counts))
## [1] TRUE
colData $condition <- factor(colData $condition)
table(colData$condition)
## 
##    cancer treatment 
##         2         2
dds <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(countData = counts , colData = colData, design = ~condition)
dds <- dds[rowSums(counts(dds)) > 10, ]
dds <- DESeq(dds)
## estimating size factors
## estimating dispersions
## gene-wise dispersion estimates
## mean-dispersion relationship
## final dispersion estimates
## fitting model and testing
res <- results(dds)
head(results(dds, tidy=TRUE))
# summary(res)
head(res)

par(mfrow=c(2,3))

plotCounts(dds, gene="ENSG00000142611", intgroup="condition")
plotCounts(dds, gene="ENSG00000157911", intgroup="condition")
plotCounts(dds, gene="ENSG00000142655", intgroup="condition")
plotCounts(dds, gene="ENSG00000149527", intgroup="condition")
plotCounts(dds, gene="ENSG00000171621", intgroup="condition")
plotCounts(dds, gene="ENSG00000272235", intgroup="condition")

par(mfrow=c(1,1))

with(res, plot(log2FoldChange, -log10(pvalue), pch=20, main="Volcano plot", xlim=c(-3,3)))


with(subset(res, padj<.01 ), points(log2FoldChange, -log10(pvalue), pch=20, col="blue"))
with(subset(res, padj<.01 & abs(log2FoldChange)>2), points(log2FoldChange, -log10(pvalue), pch=20, col="red"))

vsdata <- vst(dds, blind=FALSE)

plotPCA(vsdata, intgroup="condition") 
## using ntop=500 top features by variance

library(pheatmap)

top_genes <- head(order(res$padj), 25)

rld <- rlog(dds)
pheatmap(assay(rld)[top_genes, ])

plotMA(res, main = "DESeq2 MA plot")
